HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 322
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Lena Josephine
Balesteri Davis of Franklin.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Lena Josephine Balesteri Davis; and
WHEREAS, Lena Davis was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, born to Santo and Frances Romero Balesteri in Monterey, California, Mrs.
Davis was a graduate of Monterey High School; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Davis worked in accounting and served as an executive administrative
assistant to presidents of Chicago Printed String (CPS) formerly of Franklin; she retired from
CPS in 2000; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to her family, Lena Davis always endeavored to remain true
to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Davis enjoyed the loving companionship of her husband, Walter J.
"Joey" Davis, for sixty-three years and was the proud mother of James (Phoebe) Davis, Richard
(Julie) Davis, and Todd (Vivian) Davis; grandmother of Calvin (McKenzie) Davis, Cody (Keri)
Davis, Joshua Davis, and Sarah Davis; and great-grandmother of Hutton Joseph Davis; and
WHEREAS, Lena Davis is further survived by her sisters-in-law, Betsy (Mark) DeShano
and Barbara Bourque; nieces and nephews, Melissa Paulk, Sandy Balesteri, Louise Balesteri,
John Balesteri, Tim Davis, Crystal Karlen, James DeShano, Carole DeShano, John DeShano,
Bobby Tabiayo, and Linda Tabiayo; and dedicated caregivers, Lotta Petty and Samantha
Popodopulous; and
